Today something happened that left me feeling scared and vulnerable. I regularly watch & follow your yoga videos and today I decided to start this challenge. Something inside me said that I don‚Äôt want to be afraid anymore of circumstances & need to take care of the person I really am.

This program kicked me off on a journey for sure! I completed this and 3 other yoga programs this year (all yours!) and I can't begin to explain how much it has changed me!!! Physically (I'm developing abs!? ME?!), but mostly mentally and spiritually. I learned an important tool for my anxiety, depression, anger.. I've sharpened my discipline but have learned to be a lot kinder to myself at the same time. And there are at least 3 poses (crow is most important one!) that I used to shrug off as "I can't do that one" and wait for the next pose, but I think your most important lesson to me this year was to just try a little each day.. and it paid off incredibly! I've vowed to make it a motto of mine so I can further enjoy life, doing things I "couldn't" before. Going to be "circling back" to this program one more time to kick off an even better year! Thank you so much Adriene for all you do to better our lives!!

Adriene, I am so grateful for the love and intention that is deliciously wrapped in everything you do! I discovered you a few years ago, when my soulmate, Paul, shared one of your videos with me. Formerly, I had a regular yoga practice, and I also regularly hiked, skied, snowshoed, and backpacked in Colorado's beloved Rocky Mountains. Then, several years of chronic grief, over losses of most of my family and many dear friends to death, triggered severe chronic pain, and deep sadness and despair. In 2015, Paul came into my life and so did YOU! It still took me awhile to fully embrace what you have to offer, as more tragic deaths occurred in my life, and it was hard to pull myself together. But for over a year now, I have been regularly practicing many of your yoga videos for chronic neck and back pain, fibromyalgia, anxiety, depression, and more. I do your yoga flows on my lunch breaks at work, and also at home. Your practice is a perfect complement to my other healing practices (meditation, acupuncture, 21st Century Energy Healing, Quantum Touch, Reiki, EFT, and counseling). As a result, this year, I feel the best I've felt in my life! While I still deal with some physical pain, and, yes, I still deeply miss my departed loved ones (I would love anything you have to offer to help release grief), I've set an intention that 2018 is my year to become my TRUE authentic self again. During one of the many discussions, we got to discussing what the riders do to make themselves more supple - it is no good suppling the horse and the rider is stiff and blocking him.

Soon we were discussing Yoga with Adrienne. üòÑ
I joined a year or so ago at a friends suggestion.
And when I raised it on the group it turns out Shana is a fan too!

Last night she came up with the idea of a pop up group for the month of January to get the Artistic Dressage members to try your TRUE 30 days of Yoga.

https://www.facebook.com/groups/TRUEyogawithartisticdressage/

Here is our group link.
We will be sharing your daily links to the daily practice and offering our riders support in the challenge.

It would be absolutely AWESOME if you would join our group with us, and see how many lives you will touch with your awesome practice!

We are all very excited to get started!
